    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect indexing and missing conjugation in UL reference signal generation\n\n### Summary\nThe `generate_ul_ref_sigs_rx` function in the LTE uplink reference signal module had several critical issues that caused incorrect channel estimation during uplink processing. The function was supposed to generate complex conjugated Zadoff-Chu sequences quantized to QPSK format, but instead produced identical output to `generate_ul_ref_sigs`.\n\nThis led to incorrect channel estimation results, causing uplink demodulation failures and significantly degraded uplink throughput. Users observed high BLER and frequent uplink retransmissions when running OAI eNB with UEs transmitting on multiple resource blocks.\n\nThe root cause was threefold:\n1. Inconsistent array indexing in the debug print statement used `n<<2` instead of `n<<1`\n2. Missing complex conjugation of the reference sequences\n3. Missing QPSK quantization of the reference values\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_REFSIG/lte_ul_ref.c`: \n  * Added complex conjugation by negating imaginary components\n  * Implemented QPSK quantization to map values to +/-32767\n  * Fixed indexing inconsistency in debug print from `n<<2` to `n<<1`\n  * Corrected memory deallocation size to match allocation\n"
}